WEBVTT

00:05.672 --> 00:10.809
(GHOSTLY VOCALIZING)

00:12.278 --> 00:14.613
<i>♪</i>

00:14.948 --> 00:17.850
(RAP BEAT PLAYING)

00:17.852 --> 00:20.052
<i>♪</i>

00:20.054 --> 00:21.787
(HARD ROCK PLAYING)

00:21.789 --> 00:23.255
(SCREAMING)

00:23.257 --> 00:25.424
<i>♪</i>

00:28.294 --> 00:30.662
<i>♪</i>

00:36.603 --> 00:38.637
(WOLF HOWLING)

00:39.139 --> 00:43.075
<i>♪ Now that Dracula's</i>
<i>gone away</i>

00:43.077 --> 00:48.280
<i>♪ Mavis thought</i>
<i>this was her day</i>

00:49.015 --> 00:52.184
This could have
been her day, man!

00:53.119 --> 00:55.087
(TRUMPET PLAYING)

00:55.089 --> 00:56.989
<i>♪ But instead of living large</i>

00:56.991 --> 00:59.224
<i>♪ And finally</i>
<i>being in charge</i>

00:59.226 --> 01:01.527
<i>♪ La la lay, la la lay</i>
<i>la laaaaaa</i>

01:01.529 --> 01:04.663
<i>♪ Her father,</i>
<i>summoned-his-sister</i>

01:04.665 --> 01:06.265
<i>♪ The-evil-and-the-sinister</i>

01:06.267 --> 01:09.635
<i>♪ La la lay,</i>
<i>la la lay, la laaaaaa</i>

01:09.903 --> 01:13.939
Lydia, the Dark Baroness.

01:14.674 --> 01:17.643
(CLUCKING MUSICALLY)

01:19.245 --> 01:23.449
<i>♪ And that</i>
<i>is where we begin ♪</i>

01:24.751 --> 01:26.919
(BARKING AND CHEERING)

01:26.921 --> 01:27.853
(SCREAMING)

01:27.855 --> 01:31.290
Wendy, how did you get stuck
in a ketchup bottle?

01:31.292 --> 01:32.357
(VOICE ECHOING)
I can't help myself.

01:32.359 --> 01:34.893
The crusty bits at
the bottom are the best part.

01:34.895 --> 01:38.130
(VOCALIZING
FRENCH NATIONAL ANTHEM)

01:43.870 --> 01:45.704
(SCREAMING)

01:45.905 --> 01:47.406
(GROWLING)

01:47.408 --> 01:50.809
QUASIMODO:
Stay out of my kitchen!
MAVIS: Sorry! Sorry!

01:51.878 --> 01:53.879
(SCREAMING)

01:54.247 --> 01:55.247
Whoa!

01:55.249 --> 01:55.948
Hey, Mavis!

01:55.950 --> 01:58.917
Did you hear that
Gretchen Squib
from Scream-cation

01:58.919 --> 02:01.453
is comin' to review
the hotel today?

02:01.455 --> 02:04.356
Today?
(SCREAMING)

02:04.591 --> 02:08.426
One bad review
and she can sink a hotel!

02:08.429 --> 02:10.562
(SCREAMING)

02:11.264 --> 02:11.864
Aunt Lydia demanded I...

02:11.866 --> 02:15.200
(IMPERSONATING LYDIA)
"...maintain order..."
so nothing goes wrong,

02:15.202 --> 02:17.769
which really
just means "do nothing."

02:17.771 --> 02:20.672
But you're not gonna do that?

02:20.674 --> 02:21.473
Of course not.

02:21.475 --> 02:23.575
I'll fix up the hotel myself,
nail the review,

02:23.577 --> 02:27.713
land us a five-skull rating,
and score all the credit!

02:27.715 --> 02:29.548
Boom drac-alacka!

02:29.782 --> 02:33.152
Not that I don't totally
believe in you, Mavis,
because I do,

02:33.154 --> 02:34.987
but this just sounds
like the kind of thing

02:34.989 --> 02:36.955
that always blows up
right in your face.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.925
Oh, come on,
how's this gonna...

02:39.927 --> 02:41.393
(BARKING)

02:42.729 --> 02:44.630
(SCREAMING)

02:44.632 --> 02:46.198
(BARKING)

02:51.738 --> 02:54.573
Totally gonna
blow up in her face.

02:54.575 --> 02:56.642
(BARKING)

02:56.976 --> 02:58.844
(BARKING MEEKLY)

02:59.612 --> 03:01.313
Huh, you were right, Pedro.

03:01.315 --> 03:04.483
There is a kazoo wedged
inside your brain.

03:06.853 --> 03:07.619
Told ya.

03:07.621 --> 03:10.255
(BARKING)
(SCREAMING)

03:12.058 --> 03:15.127
Hey, girls.
Hey, Hank and Pedro!

03:15.129 --> 03:18.363
(COUGHING)
Where do you think
you're going?

03:19.399 --> 03:21.900
(LAUGHING AND KAZOO SOUNDING)

03:21.902 --> 03:24.436
Wait a sec, where's Winnie?

03:24.704 --> 03:26.605
Careful with that statue!

03:26.607 --> 03:30.275
Oh, so terrifyingly beautiful.

03:34.948 --> 03:36.148
(BARKING)
(CLUCKING)

03:36.150 --> 03:38.517
(BARKING)
(SCREAMING)

03:39.018 --> 03:40.686
(GROWLING)

03:41.521 --> 03:43.288
(BARKING)

03:44.857 --> 03:47.025
(BARKING)
(SCREAMING)

03:49.929 --> 03:51.630
(ROARING)

03:52.865 --> 03:55.033
(GRUNTING)

03:55.668 --> 03:57.436
LYDIA: Ahem, ahem.

03:57.737 --> 03:59.004
Aunt Lydia! Hi!

03:59.006 --> 04:02.441
I was just...
getting us ready
for the review.

04:02.443 --> 04:05.143
You know, with my Dad away
at the vampire council,

04:05.145 --> 04:06.712
I'm, like,
basically in charge.

04:06.714 --> 04:10.382
Except you are not
in charge. I am.

04:10.384 --> 04:13.118
That's why I said,
"like, basically?"

04:13.120 --> 04:17.055
Anyway,
I'm maintaining order. Look!

04:17.057 --> 04:18.490
I found all but one wolf pup,

04:18.492 --> 04:20.524
and when you think
about how many there are,

04:20.527 --> 04:21.627
that's really pretty good.

04:21.629 --> 04:23.595
Young lady,
Hotel Transylvania

04:23.597 --> 04:27.799
has had a sterling reputation
for a thousand years.

04:27.801 --> 04:30.068
Loose wolf pups upset order.

04:30.070 --> 04:32.571
Secrets upset order.

04:32.573 --> 04:37.509
Teenage vampires upset order!

04:38.211 --> 04:43.148
Just a quick question...
Doesn't freezing people
upset order?

04:43.150 --> 04:44.983
You will maintain order,

04:44.985 --> 04:48.253
or it is puppy duty for you.

04:48.255 --> 04:52.624
No! No!
Not "Catch the Boulder!"

04:53.726 --> 04:57.729
Great, just so I'm clear,
finding the lost pup
would count

04:57.731 --> 05:00.732
as a first step
in maintaining order?

05:01.934 --> 05:03.268
(CLUCKING)

05:03.270 --> 05:05.137
(STAFF SLAMMING)

05:10.076 --> 05:11.943
I'll take that as a yes.

05:11.945 --> 05:14.179
(CHITTERING)

05:14.181 --> 05:18.083
So, again, why are you wasting
perfectly good cake?

05:18.085 --> 05:20.619
I'm not wasting it,
Hank, I'm using it.

05:20.621 --> 05:22.487
I don't have time
to hunt for the wolf pup,

05:22.489 --> 05:25.324
so I'm bringing
the wolf pup to me.

05:25.326 --> 05:27.025
With ground cake?

05:27.027 --> 05:29.061
Devil's food cake
to be precise.

05:29.063 --> 05:31.229
(IN DEEP TERRIFYING VOICE)
I'm delicious.

05:31.231 --> 05:33.131
What he said.

05:33.133 --> 05:35.567
Know who else loves cake?
Who?

05:35.569 --> 05:38.070
(GIGGLING)
PEDRO: Humans.

05:38.072 --> 05:39.938
(SCREAMING)

05:39.940 --> 05:40.539
Oh, no!

05:40.541 --> 05:41.973
PEDRO: Yep, you've got
the Nosepicker

05:41.975 --> 05:44.509
from that human
tribe across the way.

05:44.610 --> 05:47.679
Honey, have you
seen the baby?

05:47.681 --> 05:49.081
The Nosepicker.

05:49.083 --> 05:50.882
You know, I always thought
she was just a myth,

05:50.884 --> 05:55.153
like sweet potatoes
or unicorns.

05:55.155 --> 05:56.722
Who you callin'
a myth, girl?

05:56.724 --> 06:00.058
MAVIS: Holy rabies!
She went in the hotel!

06:00.060 --> 06:02.194
Aunt Lydia will freak!
(GASPING)

06:02.196 --> 06:03.862
And Winnie is following her!

06:03.864 --> 06:06.832
We've gotta find the human
before Aunt Lydia does

06:06.834 --> 06:09.534
or she'll never
believe I can run things!

06:10.269 --> 06:12.904
Five minutes
till Gretchen's here!

06:12.906 --> 06:15.507
(TIRES SCREECHING)

06:16.042 --> 06:18.777
(SNIFFING)

06:18.779 --> 06:20.379
I smell human.

06:20.381 --> 06:24.716
It has been centuries
since I've been
on a good human hunt.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.618
(CLUCKING) Centuries!

06:26.620 --> 06:31.590
If there is a human
in this hotel,
I will find it.

06:31.592 --> 06:34.359
And I will eat it!

06:35.628 --> 06:38.430
(LAUGHING)
Well, I likely won't eat it,

06:38.432 --> 06:42.367
but a scolding it will get.
(CHUCKLING)

06:44.036 --> 06:45.437
Diane! (CLAPPING)

06:45.439 --> 06:47.606
Come!
(CLUCKING)

06:55.081 --> 06:57.149
(SNIFFING)

06:58.518 --> 07:00.485
(BARKING)

07:05.291 --> 07:06.625
(CRINKLING)

07:06.627 --> 07:08.527
(CRINKLING)

07:09.762 --> 07:12.631
Just put it in
your mouth already.

07:13.499 --> 07:15.100
(BARKING)

07:15.102 --> 07:18.370
(GASPING)
The Nosepicker and Winnie.

07:18.372 --> 07:20.405
It's a two-for-one.

07:21.741 --> 07:23.909
(PANTING)

07:25.077 --> 07:27.112
Go on without me!

07:35.455 --> 07:36.621
Gotcha!

07:36.623 --> 07:38.457
(GIGGLING)

07:38.558 --> 07:40.892
(PANTING)
(BARKING)

07:42.328 --> 07:44.062
(GIGGLING)

07:45.364 --> 07:46.665
LYDIA: Where is that human?

07:46.667 --> 07:50.635
Shush! Aunt Lydia is coming.
We've gotta hide you.

07:56.075 --> 07:57.375
It's very close!

07:57.377 --> 07:58.944
Mavis!
(WHISTLING)

07:58.946 --> 08:01.279
What are you hiding?

08:02.315 --> 08:03.582
Fine.

08:03.584 --> 08:07.886
I guess he must've found it
outside and rode in on it.

08:07.888 --> 08:08.753
Good thing I caught him,

08:08.755 --> 08:11.790
so he couldn't upset
the order of the hotel, huh?

08:11.792 --> 08:16.661
(SNIFFING) And I guess this
explains the human smell.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.663
Order maintained.

08:18.665 --> 08:21.299
(ROARING) Very well.

08:21.301 --> 08:23.134
(HORN HONKING)
We shall incinerate it

08:23.136 --> 08:28.073
before any of the guests catch
it's disgusting human scent.

08:28.474 --> 08:29.708
(ROARING)

08:29.710 --> 08:31.877
Wait, wait! (CLUCKING)

08:31.978 --> 08:32.878
Pretty car! (CLUCKING)

08:32.880 --> 08:37.549
Fine. Well, I guess
if it makes you
feel like a chick again...

08:37.551 --> 08:39.183
(CLUCKING)

08:39.186 --> 08:41.720
(CLUCKING)
(HORN HONKING)

08:42.889 --> 08:44.089
She's here!

08:44.091 --> 08:46.124
I'm here!

08:46.126 --> 08:49.294
The hotel reviewer is here!
Oh, no!

08:49.296 --> 08:51.463
Nosepicker!

08:51.465 --> 08:54.065
So, where do ya think
that goes?

08:54.067 --> 08:56.001
(GIGGLING)

08:56.235 --> 08:59.704
Go to your happy place,
go to your happy place...

08:59.706 --> 09:01.573
(SCREAMING)

09:02.341 --> 09:04.309
Order not maintained.

09:04.311 --> 09:05.677
Okay, Mavis, think!

09:05.679 --> 09:09.114
There's gotta be something
worse than a three-headed dog!

09:09.116 --> 09:11.216
(GROWLING AND BARKING)

09:11.218 --> 09:15.153
Hank! Didn't you take three
years of wolf pup calling?

09:15.155 --> 09:17.055
(CLEARING THROAT)
Four years, actually.

09:17.057 --> 09:21.159
My teacher said I had
the most scarred trachea
she'd ever seen.

09:21.161 --> 09:22.994
Can you just do it, please?

09:22.996 --> 09:25.330
Okay.
(CLEARING THROAT)

09:26.032 --> 09:28.800
(TONGUE WAGGING
AND PANTING)

09:29.201 --> 09:31.336
I'm guessing
that didn't work.

09:31.804 --> 09:33.471
(BARKING)

09:38.411 --> 09:40.011
(WHIMPERING)

09:40.947 --> 09:42.914
(SCREAMING)

09:44.383 --> 09:47.619
HANK: Wait, come back.
Where are you going?

09:47.621 --> 09:49.087
Uh, body?

09:49.089 --> 09:51.189
See? No prob.

09:52.992 --> 09:54.025
Y'all know
I was faking, right?

09:54.027 --> 09:58.797
Okay, I need you guys
to get her home before
anybody finds out.

09:58.799 --> 10:00.432
(BARKING)

10:02.101 --> 10:04.636
No!
Not through the lobby!

10:04.638 --> 10:05.270
Stop!

10:05.272 --> 10:09.841
Ah! Please, no!
No more running!

10:09.843 --> 10:10.942
(SOBBING)

10:10.944 --> 10:15.246
Careful! Careful with my
beautiful statue.

10:15.248 --> 10:17.015
(BARKING)

10:27.460 --> 10:29.127
(BARKING)

10:30.096 --> 10:31.730
(GROANING)

10:31.732 --> 10:32.998
(SCREAMING)

10:33.000 --> 10:34.899
Fire, fire, fire, fire!

10:36.402 --> 10:40.005
(PANTING) Whoa!

10:40.473 --> 10:44.009
SHRUNKEN HEAD:
Announcing Gretchen Squib!

10:44.011 --> 10:46.044
What's going on here?

10:46.445 --> 10:47.712
No!

10:50.950 --> 10:54.052
(GASPING) I love it!

10:54.054 --> 10:55.120
Huh?

10:55.122 --> 10:57.255
(SCREAMING)

10:57.556 --> 10:59.457
Five skulls!

10:59.659 --> 11:01.593
Except for that. Ew.

11:01.595 --> 11:03.194
(BUZZER SOUNDING)

11:03.996 --> 11:05.563
Could be worse.

11:05.565 --> 11:06.965
Could it?

11:07.633 --> 11:09.701
(SNEEZING, KAZOO SOUNDING)

11:09.703 --> 11:12.737
Hey, I forgot about you.

11:12.739 --> 11:15.106
(KAZOO PLAYING)

11:25.251 --> 11:27.185
Here's your key,
enjoy your stay.

11:28.788 --> 11:29.854
(BARKING)

11:29.856 --> 11:31.656
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGING)

11:32.892 --> 11:35.460
Goin' up.
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGING)

11:35.462 --> 11:38.730
(ELEVATOR CREAKING)
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGING)

11:38.732 --> 11:40.932
Or down works, too.

11:44.103 --> 11:47.539
Free-range organic larvae.
Enjoy!

11:49.041 --> 11:53.478
Ugh! So many responsibilities.
This night is the worst.

11:53.480 --> 11:55.647
Mavis, pose for a Smell-fie!

11:55.649 --> 11:58.550
(FLATULENCE)
(SNIFFING)

11:58.552 --> 12:00.318
Mmm, it's blob-berry.

12:00.320 --> 12:04.389
Mavis, stop posing
for scientifically
impossible photos

12:04.391 --> 12:06.424
and get back to work.

12:08.127 --> 12:10.328
Oh. Diane!

12:10.830 --> 12:14.599
(ROARING)
Still with the painting?

12:14.601 --> 12:17.802
Chicken minions
and their ridiculous hobbies.

12:17.804 --> 12:22.540
Uh, Mavis, remember that box
we were told to never
ever-ever-ever open?

12:22.542 --> 12:24.776
Spoiler... We opened it!

12:24.910 --> 12:26.811
(MONSTROUS ROARING)

12:27.146 --> 12:29.447
And it's time for my break.

12:29.449 --> 12:30.882
(SCREECHING)

12:30.884 --> 12:31.416
(CONTENTED SIGHING)

12:31.418 --> 12:35.320
The only place where I can
get some peace and quiet...

12:35.322 --> 12:37.388
(MONSTROUS ROARING)

12:43.162 --> 12:45.830
Is this...
all my old stuff?

12:45.832 --> 12:47.899
Aw, the first mouse I caught.

12:47.901 --> 12:51.069
Stuart, you were so slow.

12:51.203 --> 12:52.237
Hansel and Gretel?

12:52.239 --> 12:53.571
(SHUDDERING) So scary.

12:53.573 --> 12:58.510
I hated how those evil kids
tormented that nice old witch.

12:58.944 --> 13:00.578
(LAUGHING)

13:00.580 --> 13:03.081
Mavis, you found me!

13:03.083 --> 13:05.750
And it only took 90 years.

13:05.752 --> 13:07.118
Okay, what's happening now?

13:07.120 --> 13:11.356
It's me! Your Debbie.
Don't you remember?

13:11.358 --> 13:12.824
I... remember.

13:12.826 --> 13:16.594
ANNOUNCER:
<i>The Fatale Corporation brings</i>
<i>you "My First Ghost Doll."</i>

13:16.596 --> 13:19.564
<i>♪ Debbie, you're terrible,</i>
<i>you make we wanna scream</i>

13:19.566 --> 13:22.834
<i>♪ My Debbie Doll</i>
<i>is really mean</i>

13:23.102 --> 13:26.104
<i>Debbie will be</i>
<i>your best friend...</i>

13:26.106 --> 13:27.572
<i>forever.</i>

13:27.574 --> 13:29.240
So, you've been playing
Hide and Shriek

13:29.242 --> 13:31.409
and waiting all this time
for me to find you?

13:31.411 --> 13:36.381
Yep. You were looking
for Debbie, right?

13:36.383 --> 13:38.917
Oh, of course, I was.

13:38.919 --> 13:40.385
I knew you wouldn't quit.

13:40.387 --> 13:42.821
A best friend would
never stop looking, right?

13:42.823 --> 13:44.455
So, what should we play next?

13:44.457 --> 13:48.526
Uh, I don't know.
You choose.
'Kay.

13:50.462 --> 13:51.696
Yeah!

13:54.867 --> 13:56.401
(LAUGHING)

14:00.339 --> 14:02.740
Debbie loves tea parties.

14:02.742 --> 14:05.710
(SIGHING CONTENTEDLY)
You know, this was kinda fun.

14:05.712 --> 14:09.347
Sometimes
it's just nice to chill
with the simple things.

14:09.349 --> 14:12.217
Not "sometimes," Mavis.
All times.

14:12.219 --> 14:15.587
So, um, can we play tomorrow?
And tomorrow's tomorrow?

14:15.589 --> 14:18.323
And tomorrow's
tomorrow's tomorrow?

14:18.791 --> 14:20.658
Uh... sure?

14:20.660 --> 14:22.627
(SNORING)

14:23.662 --> 14:27.665
Wake up, wake up, wake up!
It's time to play!

14:28.167 --> 14:29.500
Huh? Debbie?

14:29.502 --> 14:32.470
Race ya to a billion.
(GIGGLING)

14:34.840 --> 14:36.307
(GROANING)

14:36.408 --> 14:38.509
(DEBBIE VOCALIZING)

14:39.111 --> 14:41.746
(VOCALIZING, GIGGLING)

14:41.748 --> 14:43.081
Debbie loves tea parties!

14:43.083 --> 14:48.419
And what's a tea party
without finger sandwiches?

14:48.421 --> 14:50.421
Hey, come back!

14:50.689 --> 14:51.856
Hey, get outta there!

14:51.858 --> 14:54.626
I don't just let
any finger pick my nose.

14:54.628 --> 14:58.029
Uh, yesterday you
used my finger to do it.

14:58.031 --> 14:59.397
Well, you I know.

14:59.399 --> 15:02.133
Mavis, how long we
gonna keep this up for?

15:02.135 --> 15:05.136
Yeah, I'm getting pretty full
drinking all this tea.

15:05.138 --> 15:06.638
But it isn't real tea.

15:06.640 --> 15:08.640
I like to give 100%.

15:08.642 --> 15:11.743
Oh! So. my tummy
and all this tea...

15:11.745 --> 15:15.847
Come on, Debbie was
my favorite toy as a kid.

15:15.849 --> 15:17.015
She was a gift from my dad

15:17.017 --> 15:20.151
for getting an A-plus
in Sunlight Avoidance.

15:20.153 --> 15:22.120
(BOTH LAUGHING)

15:27.893 --> 15:28.359
Mavey Wavey.

15:28.361 --> 15:33.164
ANNOUNCER:
<i>The Fatale Corporation brings</i>
<i>you "My First Ghost Doll."</i>

15:33.166 --> 15:35.133
(GIGGLING)

15:35.135 --> 15:37.368
<i>Even when you don't</i>
<i>want to play ever again,</i>

15:37.370 --> 15:40.204
<i>Demented Debbie is</i>
<i>ready for more fun.</i>

15:40.206 --> 15:42.206
(CHILD SCREAMING)

15:42.208 --> 15:44.742
Daddy, Daddy,
can I have one? Please?

15:44.744 --> 15:46.678
<i>Fatale Inc. is not responsible</i>
<i>for any dolls that annoy</i>

15:46.680 --> 15:48.012
<i>and torment you until</i>
<i>the end of time and beyond.</i>

15:48.014 --> 15:52.250
<i>All dolls are no stamped it,</i>
<i>double-locked it,</i>
<i>no erasies, yours forever.</i>

15:52.252 --> 15:53.451
Sure, honey bat.

15:53.453 --> 15:56.187
What's the worst
that can happen?

15:56.488 --> 15:59.457
Um, I'm starting to think
maybe there was a reason

15:59.459 --> 16:01.693
my Dad locked all
my stuff in the attic.

16:01.695 --> 16:02.527
(DEBBIE GIGGLING)

16:02.529 --> 16:04.862
Who's ready for
a game of Hearts?

16:04.864 --> 16:07.532
Oh, Debbie,
I'd love to, but I...

16:07.534 --> 16:08.733
(ALL CLEARING THROATS)

16:08.735 --> 16:09.767
We.
We. W-E.

16:09.769 --> 16:14.572
We, sorry. We need to
go pour acid on some plants.

16:14.574 --> 16:15.940
If that's all right?

16:15.942 --> 16:18.109
Sure. Why would
that be a problem?

16:18.111 --> 16:21.279
Huh. That was easy.
See, nothing to worry about.

16:21.281 --> 16:24.549
No, nothing to worry about.
Debbie will be fine.

16:24.551 --> 16:28.953
Just like Debbie
was fine for 90 years.

16:30.589 --> 16:32.623
(SCREAMING)

16:32.625 --> 16:37.261
So, are we, um,
are you brewing up more
of that imaginary tea,

16:37.263 --> 16:41.332
or are we just sort of,
living in this space?

16:45.404 --> 16:46.904
(DEBBIE LAUGHING)

16:46.906 --> 16:47.939
(SCREAMING)

16:47.941 --> 16:49.941
Hey, keep it steady.

16:50.175 --> 16:52.110
(SCREAMING)

16:53.078 --> 16:54.212
Hot buns!

16:54.214 --> 16:56.047
(SCREAMING)

16:56.049 --> 16:58.149
Pedro, stop. Stop!

16:58.151 --> 17:00.084
PEDRO:
Put it out!

17:00.652 --> 17:03.421
Mavis!
What is the meaning of this?

17:03.423 --> 17:05.022
I swear it wasn't our fault.

17:05.025 --> 17:07.425
My ghost doll
won't leave us alone.

17:07.426 --> 17:11.162
Blaming a ghost?
How unoriginal.

17:11.164 --> 17:14.932
Not just a ghost,
but a ghost doll.

17:14.934 --> 17:16.934
(GROWLING)

17:16.935 --> 17:18.301
Not helping.

17:18.304 --> 17:19.369
(CHUCKLING NERVOUSLY)

17:19.372 --> 17:23.107
Clean up this mess or else.

17:23.976 --> 17:25.810
(CLUCKING) Like it?

17:27.046 --> 17:28.378
(SIGHING)

17:28.381 --> 17:33.518
Man, I like how she didn't say
what she was gonna do there.

17:33.520 --> 17:35.453
A nice touch.
Totally terrifying.

17:35.455 --> 17:39.090
We've got to get
rid of Debbie!
She's wrecking everything.

17:39.092 --> 17:42.827
(EXCLAIMING)
How much fun was that?

17:42.829 --> 17:43.928
Debbie, enough.

17:43.930 --> 17:45.463
I can't play with you
all the time.

17:45.465 --> 17:48.599
I think we need
to take a break, okay?

17:48.601 --> 17:50.935
'Kay.
Break over!

17:50.937 --> 17:52.637
Tag, you're it.
(LAUGHING)

17:52.639 --> 17:54.939
(GROWLING)
Debbie just won't quit.

17:54.941 --> 17:57.175
There's no place to hide.

17:57.342 --> 17:59.410
Hang on. Hide.

17:59.412 --> 18:01.913
So, Debbie wants to play, huh?

18:01.915 --> 18:04.015
Come on, guys.

18:04.017 --> 18:07.418
9,999, 10,000.

18:07.420 --> 18:08.753
Dead or not, here I come.

18:08.755 --> 18:11.689
I don't get it. I thought
you didn't want to play

18:11.691 --> 18:13.057
with that
demented doll anymore.

18:13.059 --> 18:17.295
Pedro, we're playing
Hide and Shriek
to get rid of her.

18:17.297 --> 18:20.164
Oh, yeah, right.
Of course.

18:20.332 --> 18:22.600
So, shouldn't
we go looking for her?

18:22.835 --> 18:25.369
I do feel kinda bad
ditching her, though.

18:25.371 --> 18:27.605
She was like
my oldest friend.

18:27.607 --> 18:31.843
So sorry, I'm late.
Somehow I got
stuck in a coffin

18:31.845 --> 18:33.544
at the bottom of
a quicksand pool.

18:33.546 --> 18:36.647
Strange, no idea how
that happened.

18:36.649 --> 18:40.451
But nothing can stop me
from hanging with my Mavis.

18:40.453 --> 18:46.691
Dude, she's just a toy,
a really, really
annoying, toy.

18:46.693 --> 18:49.527
That's for sure.
(YAWNING)

18:49.529 --> 18:52.096
I'm going to go take a nap.

18:52.098 --> 18:55.967
I'm gonna do a whole
lot of nothing.

18:55.969 --> 19:00.104
I'm gonna... just go.

19:01.540 --> 19:04.142
Mavis' new friends are
trying to brainwash her.

19:04.144 --> 19:07.011
But soon everyone
will like Debbie.

19:07.013 --> 19:09.747
(LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

19:10.249 --> 19:11.282
(COUGHING)

19:11.284 --> 19:14.485
Phew!
Thought she'd never leave.

19:15.821 --> 19:16.554
(YAWNING)

19:16.556 --> 19:18.289
Hey, have you seen Hank,
Pedro or Wendy?

19:18.291 --> 19:21.926
We were supposed
to go see that new
horror flick, <i>Human Shoe.</i>

19:21.928 --> 19:25.296
NARRATOR: <i>Human Shoe.</i>
<i>It's coming...</i>

19:25.664 --> 19:27.698
<i>to kick your butt.</i>

19:27.700 --> 19:29.233
(SCREAMING)

19:29.235 --> 19:30.701
(GRUNTING) I don't know.

19:30.703 --> 19:33.137
Thanks.
You're a big help.

19:33.139 --> 19:34.372
HANK: Help.

19:34.374 --> 19:35.606
Hank?

19:37.109 --> 19:38.576
WENDY: Help!

19:39.411 --> 19:41.846
PEDRO:
Somebody help us.

19:41.947 --> 19:42.847
Mavis, help.

19:42.849 --> 19:44.882
Debbie is throwing us
a never-ending tea party.

19:44.884 --> 19:46.617
She says we're going
to be here forever.

19:46.619 --> 19:50.454
Yeah. She wants to play
with us all the time.

19:50.456 --> 19:54.158
Aw, yeah, well,
that is kinda sweet.

19:54.160 --> 19:55.393
No!
This is torture!

19:55.395 --> 20:00.631
She only has fake chamomile
and these costumes
are super itchy!

20:00.633 --> 20:02.900
Oh, I can help with that.

20:03.702 --> 20:08.272
(LAUGHING)
Yeah. Thanks dude.

20:09.441 --> 20:10.808
Wait a minute.

20:10.810 --> 20:12.843
If your arm could scratch me,

20:12.845 --> 20:14.679
why didn't you just
use it to untie us?

20:14.681 --> 20:18.182
Sometimes it's nice to be
invited to a fancy party.

20:18.184 --> 20:18.683
Right?

20:18.685 --> 20:21.319
DEBBIE:
Be right there, new friends.

20:21.321 --> 20:24.255
You know how Debbie
hates to be alone.

20:24.257 --> 20:25.156
She's coming.

20:25.158 --> 20:27.558
Mavis, you gotta
get us outta here.

20:27.560 --> 20:28.626
Puce is not my color.

20:28.628 --> 20:32.830
We'll be trapped
for all time like the girl
in the commercial.

20:32.832 --> 20:36.033
<i>♪ It's been</i>
<i>eight hundred years</i>

20:36.035 --> 20:40.171
<i>♪ Debbie's batteries</i>
<i>last forever</i>

20:40.173 --> 20:42.707
<i>♪ I'm starting to think</i>

20:42.709 --> 20:47.078
<i>♪ She's the worst gift ever</i>

20:47.080 --> 20:50.548
<i>I'm never gonna leave!</i>

20:50.849 --> 20:55.152
Debbie hates to be alone, huh?
Be right bat.

20:55.154 --> 20:56.254
(SCREECHING)

20:56.256 --> 20:57.622
Please hurry.

20:57.624 --> 20:58.723
I'm back!

20:58.725 --> 21:00.224
Debbie found these
chocolate treats

21:00.226 --> 21:02.426
at the bottom of a rat's nest.

21:04.896 --> 21:08.566
Too salty.
This tea party stinks!

21:08.568 --> 21:11.535
Hey.
(GASPING) Mavis.

21:11.537 --> 21:12.536
You made it.

21:12.538 --> 21:14.705
(CHUCKLING NERVOUSLY)
Hi. Yeah.

21:14.707 --> 21:15.640
I just had to wrap my gift.

21:15.642 --> 21:19.443
Can't come to a tea party
without a present
for the host.

21:19.445 --> 21:20.211
(SIGHING)

21:20.213 --> 21:24.448
So, you do understand
tea party protocol.

21:25.083 --> 21:28.185
Debbie thinks we're going
to be best friends...

21:28.187 --> 21:29.687
forever!

21:29.689 --> 21:30.488
(SCREAMING)

21:30.490 --> 21:33.190
I got you your
very own Debbie doll.

21:33.192 --> 21:34.625
Don't you just love it?

21:34.627 --> 21:36.394
Get it off!
Take it back!

21:36.396 --> 21:37.495
Get her away from me!

21:37.497 --> 21:39.997
But, Debbie, don't you see,
now you've got someone to

21:39.999 --> 21:44.001
"stamped it, double-locked it,
no erasies" play with forever.

21:44.003 --> 21:46.304
So, you'll never be alone.

21:46.306 --> 21:48.739
Where you going?
(LAUGHING)

21:48.741 --> 21:52.143
See that?
If you can't beat 'em,
buy another one.

21:52.145 --> 21:56.714
Wow, you really are
the worst at giving gifts.

21:58.083 --> 22:00.718
Hey, wait.
Oh, come on!

22:00.720 --> 22:02.353
At least toss me
another one of them

22:02.355 --> 22:05.189
not so delicious
chocolate balls!

22:06.391 --> 22:08.459
<i>♪</i>
